# Regional Director of Service Delivery Integration and Compliance

**Position Type:** Full-Time, Exempt  
**Reports To:** Executive Director  
**Location:** San Antonio (with regional oversight responsibilities)  
**FLSA Status:** Exempt

---

## POSITION SUMMARY

The Regional Director of Service Delivery Integration and Compliance serves as the agency's chief architect of service delivery systems across our Texas region, ensuring that complex regulatory requirements become streamlined pathways to quality care. This executive-level position combines deep regulatory expertise with systems thinking to create the infrastructure that enables exceptional service delivery across all T3C Service Packages.

As Regional Director, you will transform regulatory complexity into operational clarity, designing and implementing comprehensive frameworks that ensure compliance while maximizing efficiency. Your regional oversight encompasses both Dallas and San Antonio operations, positioning you as a key member of the leadership team with influence that extends across all service delivery systems.

This position represents a strategic investment in organizational infrastructure, recognizing that sustainable excellence requires intentional system design, proactive compliance management, and continuous quality improvement—all areas where analytical expertise and regulatory knowledge converge to create meaningful impact at the regional level.

---

## T3C INFRASTRUCTURE FUNCTION ALIGNMENT

This position contributes significantly to multiple T3C Infrastructure Functions through strategic process design and regional system oversight:

* **Cross-System Coordination** \- Architecting seamless integration across service systems throughout the region  
* **Continuous Quality Assurance and Improvement Program** \- Building infrastructure for sustained excellence  
* **Service Delivery Integration** \- Creating frameworks that enable effective care coordination across locations

---

## ESSENTIAL RESPONSIBILITIES

### Regulatory Compliance and System Navigation

The foundation of exceptional service delivery rests on comprehensive understanding and strategic application of regulatory requirements. As Regional Director, you will serve as the agency's foremost expert on compliance matters, translating complex regulations into practical, actionable frameworks that work across multiple locations.

**Compliance Architecture and Regional Oversight**

Your expertise will shape how the entire organization approaches compliance, moving from reactive responses to proactive excellence:

* Serve as agency's primary regulatory compliance expert with regional authority, maintaining current knowledge of all federal, state, and contractual requirements  
* Design and maintain comprehensive compliance tracking systems that provide real-time visibility across all service areas and locations  
* Monitor and interpret regulatory changes from DFPS, HHSC, TAC Chapter 749, and T3C requirements, ensuring organizational readiness  
* Create innovative compliance frameworks that transform complex regulations into clear, actionable processes for staff implementation  
* Conduct systematic compliance audits using risk-based approaches and develop corrective action protocols that prevent recurrence  
* Serve as primary executive liaison with regulatory bodies during reviews, inspections, and collaborative improvement initiatives

**Multi-System Integration Excellence**

The complexity of modern child welfare requires sophisticated coordination across multiple service systems. As Regional Director, you will architect the processes that make this coordination seamless across all locations:

* Design comprehensive cross-system coordination processes for STAR Health, HHSC Behavioral Health, educational systems, and community services  
* Create intuitive system navigation tools and resources that empower staff across the region to access services efficiently  
* Develop sophisticated service authorization tracking mechanisms with built-in alerts for denial patterns and resolution protocols  
* Build and maintain comprehensive provider network databases with relationship mapping and performance metrics  
* Ensure all Service Package requirements are thoughtfully embedded in operational processes with clear accountability measures

### Quality Assurance Systems Development

Quality in child welfare requires both systematic infrastructure and meticulous attention to individual case documentation. As Regional Director, you will establish comprehensive quality assurance systems that ensure excellence at every level, from individual case files to organization-wide compliance.

**Case File Auditing and Review Systems**

Your direct involvement in quality assurance includes hands-on file auditing while building systems that enhance this critical function:

* Conduct direct audits of case files to ensure documentation meets all regulatory requirements and quality standards  
* Develop comprehensive policies and procedures that standardize file documentation across all programs and locations  
* Create innovative system developments that enhance the speed and accuracy of case file reviews, including automated checklists and smart auditing tools  
* Design risk-based auditing protocols that focus resources on high-priority areas while maintaining comprehensive oversight  
* Build electronic auditing systems that track patterns, identify training needs, and prevent documentation deficiencies  
* Establish peer review processes that promote consistent quality while building organizational capacity  
* Transform audit findings into actionable improvements that prevent future deficiencies

**Infrastructure Design and Implementation**

Building quality systems requires both strategic vision and practical application at the regional level:

* Architect comprehensive quality assurance systems that monitor service delivery effectiveness across all programs  
* Develop streamlined file review protocols that reduce auditing time while increasing accuracy  
* Create audit-ready documentation templates that guide staff toward compliance from the start  
* Design automated tracking systems that flag incomplete documentation before it becomes a deficiency  
* Build sophisticated early warning systems that identify patterns in documentation quality  
* Implement continuous monitoring processes that maintain quality between formal audits

**Process Standardization and Optimization**

Consistency and efficiency emerge from well-designed processes that respect both regulatory requirements and operational realities:

* Create standardized processes for service coordination that maintain quality while reducing administrative burden  
* Design efficiency improvements using lean principles adapted to child welfare contexts  
* Develop evidence-based best practice protocols that integrate regulatory requirements with clinical excellence  
* Build decision-support tools that guide staff through complex service coordination scenarios  
* Establish continuous feedback loops that refine processes based on real-world implementation

### Data Systems and Performance Analytics

In today's data-driven environment, the ability to collect, analyze, and act on information determines organizational success. As Regional Director, you will create the systems that transform data into insights and insights into improved outcomes across the region.

**System Architecture Excellence**

* Design comprehensive data collection frameworks that capture meaningful metrics without creating documentation burden  
* Create dynamic dashboards and visualization tools providing real-time visibility into performance across all programs and locations  
* Develop sophisticated Logic Models and outcome tracking systems for each Service Package that demonstrate regional impact  
* Build automated reporting systems that deliver customized information to internal and external stakeholders  
* Implement data governance protocols ensuring accuracy, security, and appropriate access across all systems

**Performance Analysis and Strategic Insights**

Your analytical expertise will illuminate patterns and opportunities that drive organizational improvement:

* Analyze complex service delivery patterns using advanced statistical methods to identify improvement opportunities  
* Create comprehensive reports that tell the story behind the numbers for boards, funders, and regulatory bodies  
* Develop predictive models that enable proactive intervention before challenges become crises  
* Translate complex analytical findings into clear, actionable insights that drive executive decisions  
* Design sophisticated exception reporting systems that immediately flag critical issues requiring attention

### Service Integration and Coordination

Excellence in service delivery requires seamless coordination across internal departments and external systems. Your work as Regional Director will create the frameworks that enable this integration while maintaining appropriate boundaries and accountability.

**Cross-System Process Design**

* Develop elegant workflows that coordinate services across multiple internal departments and external systems  
* Create clear communication protocols that ensure information flows efficiently while protecting confidentiality  
* Design comprehensive tracking systems for service requests, authorizations, and outcomes with built-in performance metrics  
* Build resource allocation frameworks that match service availability with client needs using data-driven approaches  
* Develop robust contingency processes that maintain service continuity when primary options encounter barriers

**External Stakeholder Interface**

Your regulatory expertise and executive presence make you ideally suited to represent the agency in high-level technical discussions:

* Serve as executive technical expert in regional meetings with DFPS, HHSC, and other regulatory bodies  
* Design collaborative frameworks with external service providers that clarify roles and enhance coordination  
* Create information sharing protocols that balance transparency with privacy requirements  
* Build strategic relationships with system partners focused on mutual process improvement  
* Represent agency expertise in statewide workgroups, contributing to policy development and best practice dissemination

### Continuous Improvement Leadership

True excellence requires constant evolution. Your work will establish the agency as a learning organization that continuously enhances its effectiveness through systematic improvement.

**Innovation and Excellence**

* Identify breakthrough opportunities for system enhancement through sophisticated data analysis and pattern recognition  
* Research and thoughtfully adapt best practices from leading programs nationwide  
* Design controlled pilot programs that test innovative approaches while managing risk  
* Create comprehensive feedback mechanisms that incorporate perspectives from all stakeholders  
* Build sustainability considerations into every improvement initiative from conception

## REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS

### Education and Experience

The complexity and executive nature of this role requires a unique combination of formal education and substantial experience:

* Bachelor's degree in Business Administration, Information Systems, Public Administration, Healthcare Administration, or related field (Required)  
* Master's degree in related field such as Public Policy, Healthcare Systems, or Information Management (Preferred)  
* Minimum 5 years progressive experience in regulatory compliance, quality assurance, or systems management  
* Demonstrated experience in file auditing and quality review processes  
* Extensive knowledge of Texas child welfare regulations with demonstrated ability to interpret and apply complex requirements  
* Proven expertise in process design, system architecture, and performance improvement methodologies  
* Experience with T3C requirements and implementation strongly preferred  
* Background in data analytics and visualization tools essential

### Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities

Success in this position requires a rare combination of technical expertise, analytical capability, and strategic thinking:

**Core Competencies**

* Expert-level knowledge of child welfare regulations including TAC Chapter 749, DFPS Minimum Standards, and federal requirements  
* Comprehensive understanding of case documentation requirements and quality assurance standards  
* Advanced understanding of STAR Health, HHSC Behavioral Health Services, and Texas service delivery systems  
* Sophisticated analytical capabilities with proven ability to identify patterns and derive actionable insights  
* Systems thinking expertise enabling holistic approach to complex organizational challenges  
* Advanced data analysis skills including statistical analysis and predictive modeling  
* Technical writing excellence for creating clear, comprehensive policies and procedures

**Essential Skills**

* Exceptional attention to detail in file auditing combined with ability to maintain strategic perspective  
* Advanced project management capabilities including complex, multi-stakeholder initiatives  
* Proven ability to translate intricate regulations into practical, implementable solutions  
* Expert proficiency in database management, reporting tools, and visualization platforms  
* Strategic planning skills with focus on long-term sustainability and regional impact  
* Self-directed work style requiring minimal supervision while maintaining consistent excellence  
* Executive presence and diplomatic communication skills for regulatory interactions

This Regional Director position represents a unique executive role that derives influence through expertise, system design, and regional oversight rather than traditional personnel management. Understanding these boundaries ensures optimal effectiveness while respecting organizational dynamics.

**Process and System Authority**

Your executive authority centers on systems, processes, compliance, and quality assurance—areas where your expertise directly drives organizational excellence:

* Full decision-making authority over process design, compliance frameworks, and quality system architecture across the region  
* Authority to establish and modify operational workflows based on regulatory requirements and best practices  
* Power to require process adherence and compliance across all programs through system design and policy  
* Leadership of process improvement initiatives with authority to implement changes regionally  
* Final determination on compliance interpretations and regulatory applications  
* Direct authority to conduct file audits and require corrective actions based on findings

**Collaborative Approach**

Success requires strategic collaboration while maintaining clear executive boundaries:

* Partner with Program Directors on implementation strategies while they retain staff supervision  
* Provide technical expertise and system design without direct personnel management  
* Influence organizational practices through superior process design and compelling data  
* Achieve results through system excellence that makes compliance the path of least resistance  
* Build consensus through demonstrated expertise and proven results

## WHY THIS ROLE MATTERS

The Regional Director of Service Delivery Integration and Compliance serves as the architect of organizational excellence across our Texas operations. Your work ensures that every child and family receives services through well-designed, compliant systems that maximize positive outcomes while minimizing administrative burden.

In this executive role, you transform regulatory complexity into operational clarity. Through your expertise, what others see as bureaucratic obstacles become streamlined pathways to service. Your systems ensure that staff can focus on their vital work with children and families, confident that compliance is built into every process.

This position offers the rare opportunity to apply analytical brilliance to humanitarian purpose at the regional level. Your passion for precision, excellence, and systematic thinking directly translates into better outcomes for Texas's most vulnerable children. Every process you optimize, every compliance framework you design, and every quality improvement you implement creates ripple effects that touch countless lives across the region.

For the professional who thrives on intellectual challenges, appreciates executive autonomy, and finds satisfaction in creating order from complexity, this role represents the pinnacle of system design in child welfare. Your legacy will be measured not in personnel managed but in systems that endure, compliance that protects, and quality that transforms lives throughout Texas.
